The two ubiquitous Ca2 + - dependent , <termsem="SO:0001447"> cysteine </term> proteases known as -calpain ( calpain-1 ) and m-calpain ( capain-2 ) , are the founding members of a <termsem="SO:0000704"> gene </term> family comprising 13 <termsem="SO:0000704"> genes </term> in mammals [ 1-3 ] .
