Furthermore , calpain-independent mechanisms for protecting cell viability might exist in these cell lines that are absent in early embryonic cells .
The repeated failure to achieve <termsem="SO:0000704"> gene </term> conversion of Capn2 <termsem="SO:0000817"> + </term> / - to Capn2 - / - ES cells by selection of clones in high concentrations of G418 suggests that the homozygous mutant state somehow compromises cell viability or clonal selection of ES cells .
